@page "/components/accordion"

<PageTitle>Accordion - Tavenem Blazor Framework</PageTitle>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H1">Accordion</Heading>

<p>
    The accordion component is a collection of <a href="./components/collapse">Collapse</a>
    components. There are two main versions of the component: one where only one collapse is
    permitted to be open at a time, and one where any collapse can be open or closed without regard
    for the others.
</p>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Any number open</Heading>

<p>
    The version where any component can be open is the simplest. Just wrap a set of <a
    href="./components/collapse">Collapse</a> components in a <code>div</code> (or other semantic
    element) with the <code>accordion</code> class.
</p>

<Collapse IsOpen="true" Class="align-self-stretch outlined mb-3" BodyClass="codeblock pre-razor-code">
    <TitleContent>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="accordion">
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #1">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #2">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #3">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
            </div>
        </div>
    </TitleContent>
    <ChildContent>
        @CodeFormatter.CodeToMarkup(@"<div class=""accordion"">
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #1"">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #2"">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #3"">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
</div>")
    </ChildContent>
</Collapse>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Only one open</Heading>

<p>
    To enforce just one collapse being open at once, use the <code>Accordion</code> component.
</p>

<Collapse IsOpen="true" Class="align-self-stretch outlined mb-3" BodyClass="codeblock pre-razor-code">
    <TitleContent>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <Accordion>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #1">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #2">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #3">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
            </Accordion>
        </div>
    </TitleContent>
    <ChildContent>
        @CodeFormatter.CodeToMarkup(@"<Accordion>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #1"">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #2"">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #3"">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
</Accordion>")
    </ChildContent>
</Collapse>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Dense</Heading>

<p>
    The collapses can all be made dense (limited padding) by applying the <code>dense</code> class
    directly to the accordion itself.
</p>

<Collapse Class="align-self-stretch outlined mb-3" BodyClass="codeblock pre-razor-code">
    <TitleContent>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="accordion dense">
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #1">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #2">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #3">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
            </div>
        </div>
    </TitleContent>
    <ChildContent>
        @CodeFormatter.CodeToMarkup(@"<div class=""accordion dense"">
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #1"">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #2"">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #3"">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
</div>")
    </ChildContent>
</Collapse>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Flush</Heading>

<p>
    Use the <code>flush</code> class to remove the rounded corners and the shadow.
</p>

<Collapse Class="align-self-stretch outlined mb-3" BodyClass="codeblock pre-razor-code">
    <TitleContent>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="outlined">
                <div class="accordion flush">
                    <Collapse Title="Collapse #1">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
                    <Collapse Title="Collapse #2">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
                    <Collapse Title="Collapse #3">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </TitleContent>
    <ChildContent>
        @CodeFormatter.CodeToMarkup(@"<div class=""outlined"">
    <div class=""accordion flush"">
        <Collapse Title=""Collapse #1"">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
        <Collapse Title=""Collapse #2"">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
        <Collapse Title=""Collapse #3"">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
    </div>
</div>")
    </ChildContent>
</Collapse>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Disabled</Heading>

<p>
    Set the <code>Disabled</code> property on an <code>Accordion</code> component to disable all the
    collapses. Note that this doesn't change the collapsed state of the collapses, or prevent it
    from being changed programmatically. It only prevents user interaction.
</p>

<Collapse IsOpen="true" Class="align-self-stretch outlined mb-3" BodyClass="codeblock pre-razor-code">
    <TitleContent>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <Accordion Disabled="true">
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #1">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
                <Collapse IsOpen="true" Title="Collapse #2">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
                <Collapse Title="Collapse #3">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
            </Accordion>
        </div>
    </TitleContent>
    <ChildContent>
        @CodeFormatter.CodeToMarkup(@"<Accordion Disabled=""true"">
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #1"">Collapsed content #1</Collapse>
    <Collapse IsOpen=""true"" Title=""Collapse #2"">Collapsed content #2</Collapse>
    <Collapse Title=""Collapse #3"">Collapsed content #3</Collapse>
</Accordion>")
    </ChildContent>
</Collapse>